1
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:35,030
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:37,890
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:50,039 --> 00:01:53,110
[Capital Film Studio]

4
00:01:58,390 --> 00:02:04,320
[Capital Film Studio]

5
00:02:16,610 --> 00:02:17,150
Comrade,

6
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:18,640
who are you looking for?

7
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:21,020
Hello, sir. I'm looking for Director Weng.

8
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:23,280
Director Weng? What do you want with him?

9
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:24,640
I'm sort of his student.

10
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:26,400
From the Central Academy of Drama?

11
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:26,780
Or the Beijing Film Academy?

12
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:28,900
No, no, no.
I wasn't professionally trained.

13
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:29,860
I'm from Yantai.

14
00:02:30,430 --> 00:02:31,680
I'm a playwriting enthusiast.

15
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:32,560
My name is Xu Shengli.

16
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,340
Xu, spelled X-U.

17
00:02:33,340 --> 00:02:34,410
Shengli as in "Shengli Oilfield."

18
00:02:34,410 --> 00:02:34,740
I see.

19
00:02:34,810 --> 00:02:35,620
Director Weng's student, right?

20
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:36,020
Come on.

21
00:02:36,020 --> 00:02:36,930
Come on in. Let's talk.

22
00:02:36,930 --> 00:02:38,920
[Studio]

23
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,100
At the end of last year,

24
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:41,250
Director Weng came to our factory

25
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:43,500
to experience life
at the grassroots level.

26
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,340
I served

27
00:02:45,310 --> 00:02:46,620
as a worker representative

28
00:02:46,620 --> 00:02:48,020
to assist Director Weng.

29
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,590
For that week or so,

30
00:02:50,130 --> 00:02:52,000
we kept talking and communicating.

31
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,740
Director Weng even praised me and said

32
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:54,670
I had potential,

33
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,010
and I must keep writing.

34
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:57,750
He asked me to send the script to him

35
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:58,810
once I finished it.

36
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:00,190
He said he'd show the script

37
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:01,390
to the other experts.

38
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:02,780
He said if it was good,

39
00:03:02,930 --> 00:03:04,330
it might even get filmed.

40
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:06,400
Now that my script is done,

41
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:07,620
I thought I'd come personally

42
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:08,800
to visit Director Weng

43
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,460
and also pay a visit to you all.

44
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:14,500
Did you mail it?

45
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:15,800
I did.

46
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:16,620
Zou,

47
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:17,910
look for it.

48
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,590
Young man.

49
00:03:21,650 --> 00:03:22,630
That script of yours,

50
00:03:22,630 --> 00:03:23,620
what's it called?

51
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:24,280
It's called

52
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,630
"As High as the Sky."

53
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,329
["As High as the Sky"
Author: Xu Shengli]

54
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,120
Young man,

55
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:35,360
look at our workload.

56
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:36,160
["As High as the Sky"
Author: Xu Shengli]

57
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:37,040
We're under so much pressure.

58
00:03:38,930 --> 00:03:39,530
It's fine!

59
00:03:39,710 --> 00:03:40,970
Don't bother looking for it.

60
00:03:40,970 --> 00:03:42,100
I brought a new copy.

61
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,400
I hope you can take a look

62
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:47,780
and give me some advice.

63
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:48,150
Okay.

64
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:50,329
Director Weng isn't here.

65
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:50,970
I can't tell you

66
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:51,840
where he went.

67
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:53,250
Our studio is

68
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:54,280
mainly for creative work.

69
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:54,910
You know,

70
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,410
we hate interruptions.

71
00:03:56,530 --> 00:03:57,280
When you go back,

72
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,650
contact Director Weng first.

73
00:03:58,650 --> 00:03:59,740
Come again after you reach him.

74
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:00,070
Okay?

75
00:04:00,690 --> 00:04:01,750
Yes, I got it.

76
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:04,100
Well... I'll come back next time.

77
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:05,620
See you around.

78
00:04:11,370 --> 00:04:12,900
Sir, may I ask your surname?

79
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:14,870
Me? My surname is Wu.

80
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:15,470
Mr. Wu.

81
00:04:16,769 --> 00:04:17,870
My name is Xu Shengli.

82
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:18,660
I know.

83
00:04:18,660 --> 00:04:19,920
You already said that.

84
00:04:20,769 --> 00:04:21,630
Alright, then,

85
00:04:21,930 --> 00:04:23,130
I will leave you to it.

86
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,180
When did Director Weng take on

87
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,440
such a tacky student?

88
00:04:34,770 --> 00:04:35,860
Then why didn't you tell him

89
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:36,890
that Director Weng is on a business trip?

90
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:39,390
[Movie script: "As High as the Sky"
Author: Xu Shengli]

91
00:04:37,370 --> 00:04:38,040
This guy,

92
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,240
from what I can see,

93
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,500
doesn't even have Director Weng's number

94
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:41,010
to reach him,

95
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:42,210
and he just came here like that.

96
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:43,610
I wouldn't dare tell him.

97
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,580
What he said might not be true.

98
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:46,260
Wu,

99
00:04:46,510 --> 00:04:47,810
so you chatted with him for so long

100
00:04:47,810 --> 00:04:48,870
just for material?

101
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,450
Gathering this kind of material is

102
00:04:51,450 --> 00:04:52,780
completely worthless.

103
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,300
He is just a nobody.

104
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:56,000
I agree.

105
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,250
The sleep I got last night

106
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:03,320
felt like fighting a war.

107
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:05,160
I didn't sleep a wink all night.

108
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:06,350
That jerk

109
00:05:06,380 --> 00:05:07,780
really messed things up.

110
00:05:07,950 --> 00:05:09,040
My half-day's pay...

111
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,620
I just slept right through it.

112
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:11,390
What kind of place is this

113
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,850
that you've brought me to?

114
00:05:14,860 --> 00:05:15,920
I told you

115
00:05:15,950 --> 00:05:17,100
I wanted a single room upstairs.

116
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,960
I don't want to live in a basement.

117
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:28,680
Yeah.

118
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:31,010
But the rooms upstairs are full.

119
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,360
Since you're already here,

120
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,430
let me show you around.

121
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:34,190
You need to shop around

122
00:05:34,190 --> 00:05:35,680
even when buying something.

123
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,540
Where did you go?

124
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:37,770
He saw a pretty girl.

125
00:05:37,810 --> 00:05:39,270
The big peacock wants to strut his stuff.

126
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:40,470
This is the washroom.

127
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:41,870
The hot water room is over here,

128
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:43,920
offering hot water around the clock.

129
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,620
-The four directions...
-I'm heading out for jobs.

130
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:46,750
Help me take my stuff back.

131
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:47,640
Take care, bro.

132
00:05:48,659 --> 00:05:49,430
Have you ever seen a basement

133
00:05:49,430 --> 00:05:50,830
with such good sunlight?

134
00:05:51,370 --> 00:05:52,060
The sun also shines

135
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,659
over there in the afternoon.

136
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:54,740
Twice a day.

137
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,040
My place is rated

138
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,220
a hygiene model every year

139
00:05:57,220 --> 00:05:59,270
with high tenant satisfaction.

140
00:06:38,810 --> 00:06:39,550
Artist.

141
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:41,330
Hello, my name is Tao Liangliang.

142
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:42,260
Are you new here?

143
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:44,330
H-Hurry up and take me

144
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:45,480
to see that room.

145
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:46,950
This way.

146
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,810
There used to be

147
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,630
a student taking the dance academy exam.

148
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:52,400
The mother and daughter
just moved out this morning,

149
00:06:52,210 --> 00:06:54,400
[Warning: No trash in the corridors.]

150
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,480
and then you came.

151
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:53,940
Tell me,

152
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:54,730
doesn't it

153
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:57,400
[Please walk and speak quietly.]

154
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:56,810
feel like this room is meant for you?

155
00:06:57,630 --> 00:06:58,680
Come in, please.

156
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,810
Take a look around.

157
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:02,550
It's a single room, isn't it?

158
00:07:10,770 --> 00:07:12,680
I don't have many female guests here.

159
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,510
You pay for one bed

160
00:07:14,620 --> 00:07:16,130
but get a private room.

161
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:20,480
So, how much is it a day?

162
00:07:20,570 --> 00:07:21,890
Eight. Just 8.

163
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:28,760
You make it sound nice,

164
00:07:28,810 --> 00:07:29,720
but looking at it,

165
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,050
it's nothing special.

166
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:32,220
It's all dirty.

167
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:33,800
The mother and daughter

168
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,070
left in a hurry this morning.

169
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:35,860
I haven't had time

170
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:36,659
to clean up yet.

171
00:07:36,659 --> 00:07:37,740
It looks a bit messy.

172
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:38,430
Before,

173
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:38,980
they used

174
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:40,580
their own sheets and covers.

175
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:41,890
They kept the room

176
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:43,100
super neat.

177
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,159
Besides,

178
00:07:44,450 --> 00:07:46,580
if you're going to act in the future...

179
00:07:47,690 --> 00:07:49,180
Are you an actress, miss?

180
00:07:49,450 --> 00:07:50,500
That's perfect!

181
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:51,720
People living in this building are

182
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,050
all engaged in the arts.

183
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:54,440
There's an actor

184
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:55,510
in our room.

185
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:55,830
Yes.

186
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,870
There are also

187
00:07:58,070 --> 00:07:58,810
a dancer,

188
00:07:59,370 --> 00:08:00,410
a singer,

189
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,570
and a screenwriter.

190
00:08:01,570 --> 00:08:02,970
And I play the saxophone.

191
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:05,010
This kind of artistic atmosphere is

192
00:08:05,010 --> 00:08:05,870
hard to come by.

193
00:08:06,370 --> 00:08:07,300
Exactly.

194
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:08,480
Our place,

195
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:10,830
small as it is, has everything.

196
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,450
It gets a motley crew.

197
00:08:12,540 --> 00:08:13,200
Look at him,

198
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:15,120
he's not just a saxophone player,

199
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:15,740
an artist.

200
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:16,840
He's also

201
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:18,070
a Beijinger,

202
00:08:18,740 --> 00:08:19,680
a local.

203
00:08:20,450 --> 00:08:21,660
You can ask him anything

204
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:22,520
about Beijing.

205
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:25,060
You're from Beijing?

206
00:08:25,310 --> 00:08:26,240
Why are you, a local,

207
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,860
staying in a hostel?

208
00:08:28,450 --> 00:08:29,450
A-Are you two

209
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:30,810
ganging up to trick me?

210
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:31,430
No.

211
00:08:31,620 --> 00:08:33,250
Even a local lives here.

212
00:08:33,659 --> 00:08:35,870
That just proves how great this place is.

213
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:37,669
I don't stay at home. I live here.

214
00:08:37,669 --> 00:08:39,240
This place is even better than home!

215
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,789
Besides, we Beijingers

216
00:08:40,789 --> 00:08:41,940
never trick outsiders.

217
00:08:41,940 --> 00:08:42,470
We don't.

218
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,460
Just stay here.

219
00:08:43,630 --> 00:08:44,360
Listen to me.

220
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:45,390
It's perfect.

221
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:47,750
Girl, just stay here.

222
00:08:47,790 --> 00:08:49,150
It's absolutely perfect.

223
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:49,940
Don't hesitate.

224
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:51,790
Otherwise, this room will be booked
by this afternoon.

225
00:08:51,790 --> 00:08:53,250
My hostel is very popular.

226
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:54,960
Well,

227
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:56,600
if any rooms upstairs

228
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,620
become available,

229
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,480
you must let me know immediately.

230
00:09:02,530 --> 00:09:03,360
What did I tell you?

231
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,220
You'd definitely like this room.

232
00:09:05,530 --> 00:09:06,580
So, what now?

233
00:09:07,410 --> 00:09:09,860
Then I'll just stay here temporarily

234
00:09:09,890 --> 00:09:11,350
and make do with it for now.

235
00:09:11,630 --> 00:09:12,510
Alright!

236
00:09:12,890 --> 00:09:14,250
Put your luggage down, please.

237
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,980
We'll go up and register later.

238
00:09:16,210 --> 00:09:17,390
Hey, Mr. Tao.

239
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,370
Can you sort out the furniture

240
00:09:18,370 --> 00:09:19,150
and other stuff?

241
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:20,320
Leave it to me. Hurry up.

242
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,450
If you need anything, just turn to him.

243
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:26,200
Miss,

244
00:09:26,530 --> 00:09:27,730
which bed do you want?

245
00:09:28,390 --> 00:09:30,550
See if you want this side

246
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:31,360
or that side.

247
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,340
This side is

248
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:33,750
quiet.

249
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,410
And here,

250
00:09:35,940 --> 00:09:38,220
it's sunny and airy.

251
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:40,460
Anyway, both have their pros.

252
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:48,550
I've watched your show.

253
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:51,080
You just recognized me?

254
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,360
A Republic-era drama.

255
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:54,840
A wealthy young lady!

256
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,480
So pretty!

257
00:09:58,510 --> 00:10:01,170
It's just
that you were unreasonably ferocious

258
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,130
when you got angry.

259
00:10:02,130 --> 00:10:03,600
You looked pretty wild.

260
00:10:04,390 --> 00:10:04,940
But I think you...

261
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:06,550
You're quite young,

262
00:10:06,650 --> 00:10:07,770
but you went blind early.

263
00:10:07,770 --> 00:10:08,260
Get out.

264
00:10:08,530 --> 00:10:09,600
-Get out! Go!
-Wait, I...

265
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,530
I don't need your help.

266
00:10:10,530 --> 00:10:11,510
Go away.

267
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,320
-Just leave.
-I'm briefly sharing

268
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,650
my thoughts on the show.

269
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:20,710
My saxophone.

270
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:24,100
Tell me if you need anything.

271
00:10:25,930 --> 00:10:27,260
She's totally spoiled.

272
00:10:28,940 --> 00:10:30,510
Once she's worked up,

273
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:32,700
she's ferocious,

274
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:33,890
running so wild.

275
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:49,930
[Welcome to Beijing]

276
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:53,650
[No entry for vehicles.]

277
00:10:58,100 --> 00:11:03,220
[Welcome to Beijing]

278
00:11:07,740 --> 00:11:08,310
Sir!

279
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:09,230
Sir.

280
00:11:10,550 --> 00:11:11,840
Why are you squatting here?

281
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,060
I've been looking for you for a while.

282
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:17,930
[No entry for vehicles.]

283
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,410
I thought you weren't coming.

284
00:11:16,210 --> 00:11:17,390
I did have something to handle
this afternoon.

285
00:11:17,390 --> 00:11:18,120
I got held up.

286
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:19,880
Here you are.

287
00:11:20,770 --> 00:11:21,830
You found your bag?

288
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,300
Then where did you get this money?

289
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:26,650
I said I'd pay you back.

290
00:11:26,650 --> 00:11:27,850
So I definitely will.

291
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:28,360
Take it.

292
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,790
But this is too much.

293
00:11:36,410 --> 00:11:38,210
That's 20 extra for just one day.

294
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:40,010
I'm not a loan shark.

295
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:40,940
Take this back.

296
00:11:41,980 --> 00:11:42,780
Just take it.

297
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,240
You did me a big favor yesterday.

298
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,720
No need. Fifty is enough.

299
00:11:45,770 --> 00:11:46,230
Keep it.

300
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:49,130
Just take it.

301
00:11:49,290 --> 00:11:49,620
Wait.

302
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:53,730
I'm fine.

303
00:11:57,010 --> 00:11:58,080
Forget about the money.

304
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:58,880
Lean here now.

305
00:12:02,410 --> 00:12:03,560
What's up with you?

306
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,000
It's nothing.

307
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,600
I just haven't eaten all day.

308
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:10,370
Thank you.

309
00:12:16,740 --> 00:12:18,740
How are you feeling? Any better now?

310
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:20,620
Sorry,

311
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:22,330
I haven't had any food all day.

312
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:25,600
Eat these buns.

313
00:12:27,290 --> 00:12:28,030
You have some, too.

314
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:29,160
I've already eaten.

315
00:12:31,010 --> 00:12:32,130
What is wrong with you?

316
00:12:32,130 --> 00:12:33,990
You got money, but you didn't eat.

317
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:39,350
Well... Where did you get that money?

318
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:42,170
Don't worry. I didn't steal or rob.

319
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:45,890
I didn't use the money you gave me
to stay in a hotel either.

320
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,650
During the day, I handed out flyers

321
00:12:47,650 --> 00:12:48,980
and earned 10 yuan a day.

322
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:50,570
Just a second.

323
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:57,150
Last night, I was sorting books

324
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,380
together with them.

325
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,080
That was 8 yuan for 100 books.

326
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:03,230
I didn't mean to skip meals.
I just didn't have time.

327
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:08,940
You're pretty tough.

328
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:10,550
Eat this egg.

329
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:13,770
But you still need to eat.

330
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:15,120
Making money can wait.

331
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,460
By the way, sir,

332
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,260
have you settled down?

333
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:23,120
I'd like to ask you something.

334
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,010
The small hotel I found is

335
00:13:24,010 --> 00:13:25,200
quite convenient,

336
00:13:25,790 --> 00:13:27,500
but it costs over 10 yuan a day.

337
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:29,020
I really can't afford it.

338
00:13:29,890 --> 00:13:30,770
I don't even know where to get

339
00:13:30,770 --> 00:13:32,340
the money for my lesson fees.

340
00:13:32,340 --> 00:13:33,580
W-What lesson fees?

341
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:34,700
Vocal lessons.

342
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:36,420
That's 100 yuan per lesson.

343
00:13:37,010 --> 00:13:37,750
One hundred?

344
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:39,480
That is so expensive.

345
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:40,440
It's not expensive.

346
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:41,370
Private vocal lessons nowadays

347
00:13:41,370 --> 00:13:42,430
all cost this much.

348
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,480
Do you have any recommendations?

349
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,940
I mean a safe place to stay.

350
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:53,100
M-My place.

351
00:13:54,790 --> 00:13:55,270
Not my place.

352
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:56,150
Well... It is my place.

353
00:13:56,150 --> 00:13:58,250
I mean the hotel I'm staying at.

354
00:13:58,620 --> 00:13:59,720
That is pretty good.

355
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:01,130
It's in an alley and quite safe.

356
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:02,820
Most importantly, it's cheap.

357
00:14:02,820 --> 00:14:03,580
How much?

358
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:06,120
My bed is 6 yuan a day.

359
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:09,410
Okay, I'll go right now.

360
00:14:10,420 --> 00:14:11,290
Don't rush to decide.

361
00:14:11,290 --> 00:14:12,170
Go take a look first.

362
00:14:12,170 --> 00:14:13,500
Decide after you see it.

363
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:15,340
I think

364
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,320
the basic living conditions

365
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:18,580
must've been secured.

366
00:14:21,940 --> 00:14:22,340
Okay.

367
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:26,150
By the way,

368
00:14:26,370 --> 00:14:27,510
how should I address you?

369
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:28,170
Xu Shengli.

370
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,500
Xu, spelled X-U.

371
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:32,030
-Shengli
-Shengli as in "Shengli Oilfield."

372
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:33,760
Right.

373
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,480
Eat up now.

374
00:14:35,860 --> 00:14:37,480
I'll take you there to have a look
after you finish.

375
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:37,910
Okay.

376
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,160
I won't stand on ceremony, then.

377
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:45,120
Sir, you're so nice.

378
00:14:53,530 --> 00:14:54,620
Is it really okay?

379
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:55,590
No worries!

380
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,360
Should I get down?

381
00:14:57,460 --> 00:14:59,140
No need. It's still a ways off.

382
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:00,590
There's no problem.

383
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:01,220
Okay.

384
00:15:03,580 --> 00:15:04,180
It's fine.

385
00:15:05,130 --> 00:15:05,610
Look.

386
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,400
This is the Corner Tower.

387
00:15:07,620 --> 00:15:08,840
When I came to Beijing before,

388
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:09,840
I visited it once.

389
00:15:10,060 --> 00:15:11,660
Oh, you've been here before?

390
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:17,740
Here we are.

391
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,130
Give me a hand with this.

392
00:15:19,130 --> 00:15:19,460
Okay.

393
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:20,380
Be careful.

394
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:22,360
Come on, be careful.

395
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:22,890
Careful.

396
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:24,330
Good.

397
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:26,500
Little Northeasterner!

398
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,480
Get a room ready for this girl.

399
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:31,720
[Registration Room]

400
00:15:30,770 --> 00:15:31,700
What's going on?

401
00:15:32,110 --> 00:15:33,490
What do you mean, "what's going on"?

402
00:15:33,490 --> 00:15:36,540
[Registration Room]

403
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,860
From your hometown? Your classmate?

404
00:15:35,860 --> 00:15:37,660
The girl from the train station.

405
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:39,750
So it's a series.

406
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:42,300
Alright. What kind of room do you want?

407
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:44,620
Same as his is fine.

408
00:15:44,890 --> 00:15:45,750
The 6-yuan one.

409
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:48,700
Girls' rooms usually have 2

410
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:49,290
to a room,

411
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,290
or 3 at most.

412
00:15:50,550 --> 00:15:51,630
So there's no 6-yuan rate.

413
00:15:51,630 --> 00:15:52,490
It's all 8 yuan.

414
00:15:53,550 --> 00:15:54,240
Eight yuan?

415
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:58,500
Didn't you say
that referrals from regular guests

416
00:15:58,500 --> 00:15:59,700
could get a discount?

417
00:16:02,410 --> 00:16:03,370
Referrals are

418
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:04,720
definitely different.

419
00:16:04,790 --> 00:16:05,510
How about this?

420
00:16:05,510 --> 00:16:06,440
Um, you must be tired.

421
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,320
Sit there and take a rest.

422
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,720
The two of us need to talk.

423
00:16:10,610 --> 00:16:16,150
[Registration Room]

424
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:11,710
Y-You go rest a bit.

425
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:18,870
What's up?

426
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:21,770
What do you mean?

427
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:22,530
What? What's wrong?

428
00:16:22,530 --> 00:16:23,030
Well,

429
00:16:23,980 --> 00:16:25,710
are you paying the extra 2 yuan?

430
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:29,880
This girl just got to Beijing.

431
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:32,000
She had 2,000 yuan stolen.

432
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:34,350
I'm helping her and seeing it through.

433
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:35,750
I'm impressed, Mr. Xu.

434
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:37,360
I didn't know you had it in you.

435
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:38,670
You hooked up
as soon as you got to Beijing.

436
00:16:38,670 --> 00:16:39,870
Don't talk nonsense.

437
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,160
It's helping others.

438
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:42,270
Where's she from?

439
00:16:42,820 --> 00:16:43,350
Wenzhou.

440
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:44,510
What's her name?

441
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:45,150
Zhuang Zhuang.

442
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:46,530
What's she doing in Beijing?

443
00:16:46,530 --> 00:16:47,170
Learning to sing.

444
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:48,320
She says she wants to take an exam

445
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,860
for a s-song and dance troupe.

446
00:16:49,860 --> 00:16:51,460
So how did she end up with you?

447
00:16:53,050 --> 00:16:54,340
I've told you so many times!

448
00:16:54,340 --> 00:16:54,960
We two have been

449
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:56,760
to the police station together.

450
00:16:57,620 --> 00:17:00,010
She's really the one
from the train station?

451
00:17:00,010 --> 00:17:01,150
I have to ask clearly.

452
00:17:01,150 --> 00:17:02,790
What if she's a murderer or arsonist?

453
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:04,310
I can't explain it if the police come.

454
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:05,740
J-Just look at her.

455
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:06,960
How could she be a murderer or arsonist?

456
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,569
You're paying the 2 yuan, huh?

457
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,369
But you two can't live together.

458
00:17:11,109 --> 00:17:12,369
What are you thinking?

459
00:17:12,810 --> 00:17:14,400
We'll live separately!

460
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:15,839
Then what are you after?

461
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,940
I... I just want you to earn more.

462
00:17:19,940 --> 00:17:21,290
What am I after?

463
00:17:21,670 --> 00:17:22,800
[Registration Room]

464
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:24,040
Mr. Xu!

465
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:25,710
Let me add a couple of things.

466
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:28,770
Even though you're not living together,

467
00:17:28,770 --> 00:17:29,900
you can't make those kinds

468
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:31,030
of improper noises.

469
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:32,880
I'll give you some noises right now.

470
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:33,760
Don't mess with me.

471
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:34,460
Listen,

472
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:35,570
if you lay a finger on me,

473
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:36,980
I'll expose your ulterior motives

474
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:37,770
to the public.

475
00:17:37,770 --> 00:17:38,570
-W-What?
-Dare you move?

476
00:17:38,570 --> 00:17:40,050
What ulterior motives do I have?

477
00:17:40,050 --> 00:17:41,270
Miss Zhuang Zhuang!

478
00:17:42,290 --> 00:17:44,110
You're Miss Zhuang Zhuang, right?

479
00:17:44,110 --> 00:17:45,170
Sorry for the wait.

480
00:17:45,350 --> 00:17:46,310
Let's see the room.

481
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:48,090
Come check out the environment inside.

482
00:17:48,090 --> 00:17:48,660
Okay.

483
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:50,180
Hi, Luo.

484
00:17:52,350 --> 00:17:54,060
I live in this room, 108.

485
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:58,290
Can't believe you

486
00:17:58,290 --> 00:17:59,850
turned a basement into this.

487
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:01,450
Girls' rooms are over there.

488
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:03,340
D-Do you think it's too messy?

489
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:05,090
No, I think it's great.

490
00:18:05,420 --> 00:18:06,180
When I was little,

491
00:18:06,180 --> 00:18:07,180
I really envied those

492
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:08,310
who lived in dorms.

493
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,790
I didn't expect

494
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:10,660
someone as elegant as you

495
00:18:10,660 --> 00:18:11,990
to be so down-to-earth.

496
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:13,840
If not, I wouldn't even be here.

497
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:17,820
Anyone inside?

498
00:18:19,790 --> 00:18:20,680
I'm coming in!

499
00:18:28,510 --> 00:18:29,440
Come in, please.

500
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:33,990
This bed is for an actress.

501
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:35,550
For the sake of privacy,

502
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:36,810
she took the outer bed.

503
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:37,850
So you can have

504
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:39,680
the best spot here by the window.

505
00:18:39,790 --> 00:18:40,700
Even though it's a basement,

506
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,510
I can assure you that it's

507
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:42,750
warm in winter and cool in summer.

508
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,010
If you have your own bedding,

509
00:18:44,010 --> 00:18:44,810
use yours.

510
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:45,940
If not, I have some ready for you.

511
00:18:45,940 --> 00:18:47,310
I have everything. I brought it with me.

512
00:18:47,310 --> 00:18:48,570
If you think it's okay,

513
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:49,180
come upstairs

514
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:50,050
to sign an agreement with me later.

515
00:18:50,050 --> 00:18:51,160
And then you can move in.

516
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:51,990
I really like it.

517
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:52,650
Brilliant.

518
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:53,850
Let me show you

519
00:18:53,850 --> 00:18:54,660
the facilities.

520
00:18:54,660 --> 00:18:55,790
-Okay.
-Let me do it.

521
00:18:57,220 --> 00:18:58,680
That saves me the trouble.

522
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,290
If you have any questions,
just ask Mr. Xu.

523
00:19:01,290 --> 00:19:02,150
I'm off to work.

524
00:19:03,330 --> 00:19:04,420
Thank you, sir!

525
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:07,250
Didn't we pass by

526
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:08,200
the washroom earlier?

527
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,640
There's hot water and showers.

528
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:10,720
You can use them anytime.

529
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:11,780
And for cooking...

530
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,530
You still have a bag upstairs!

531
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:15,240
Um, sir...

532
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:18,380
Mr. Xu.

533
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,000
Thank you for recommending

534
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,260
such an awesome place.

535
00:19:23,380 --> 00:19:24,380
Don't mention it.

536
00:19:25,290 --> 00:19:25,900
Well,

537
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:27,680
about the money,

538
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:28,980
if I use it to pay the deposit,

539
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:30,160
can I pay you back in a couple of days?

540
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:30,910
No rush!

541
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:32,180
Really, no rush.

542
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:34,180
Just don't make yourself
faint from hunger again.

543
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:34,710
Besides,

544
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:36,160
we'll be neighbors from now on.

545
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:37,280
In half a month,

546
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:39,510
1 month, or even 2 months,
it'll all be fine.

547
00:19:39,510 --> 00:19:40,840
It won't take that long.

548
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:41,410
It won't.

549
00:19:44,010 --> 00:19:46,200
I'll tidy this place up, and it'll look

550
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,050
totally different.

551
00:19:47,050 --> 00:19:48,980
I'll invite you to take a look then.

552
00:19:49,220 --> 00:19:49,570
Okay.

553
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:50,940
T-Then you go ahead and tidy up.

554
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:51,940
I'll get your bag.

555
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:53,240
Mr. Xu.

556
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,630
I really appreciate your help.

557
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:57,810
Don't mention it.

558
00:19:57,890 --> 00:19:59,130
Just settle in.

559
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:19,240
You got this, Zhuang Zhuang.

560
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:42,250
"May you enjoy your stay here."

561
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:52,420
Hello.

562
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,020
I'm Zhuang Zhuang.

563
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:01,120
Who let you live here?

564
00:21:01,810 --> 00:21:02,410
The owner.

565
00:21:02,570 --> 00:21:03,850
He said this room

566
00:21:04,110 --> 00:21:06,770
wouldn't have anyone else,
so I decided to stay here.

567
00:21:06,770 --> 00:21:08,160
Why don't you go ask him?

568
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:09,510
I paid, too.

569
00:21:20,530 --> 00:21:21,510
You promised to give me

570
00:21:21,510 --> 00:21:22,610
a single room this morning!

571
00:21:22,610 --> 00:21:24,050
But now someone else has moved in!

572
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:25,020
What do you mean?

573
00:21:25,290 --> 00:21:26,730
Come out here and explain!

574
00:21:26,730 --> 00:21:29,190
[Registration Room]

575
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:39,720
[Registration Room]

576
00:21:34,790 --> 00:21:35,240
Miss,

577
00:21:35,550 --> 00:21:36,150
calm down.

578
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:37,240
Don't be angry.

579
00:21:37,790 --> 00:21:38,740
This morning,

580
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:40,770
your room was indeed a single.

581
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,200
But now it's not.

582
00:21:42,220 --> 00:21:43,350
Someone else arrived.

583
00:21:43,350 --> 00:21:44,950
I couldn't just kick her out.

584
00:21:45,350 --> 00:21:46,000
The main thing is,

585
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,630
our location is too good.

586
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:48,940
Business is booming.

587
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,720
There isn't a single bed left.

588
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:51,980
I really had no choice.

589
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:52,980
You big liar!

590
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:54,240
This is a shady inn!

591
00:21:54,610 --> 00:21:55,540
I'm not staying.

592
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,030
How did my place become

593
00:21:57,030 --> 00:21:58,180
a shady inn?

594
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:00,630
You've been reading too many scripts.

595
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:01,850
If you stay here,

596
00:22:01,850 --> 00:22:03,580
I can't promise anything else,

597
00:22:03,850 --> 00:22:06,310
but I can definitely
guarantee your safety.

598
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,740
Also, I don't just put

599
00:22:07,740 --> 00:22:09,000
anyone in your room.

600
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:10,220
Sketchy people

601
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:10,850
can't even get into

602
00:22:10,850 --> 00:22:12,300
this place.

603
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:13,310
Besides,

604
00:22:13,740 --> 00:22:15,960
you'll definitely be filming later.

605
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:16,900
You'll be on set.

606
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,160
You're an actress.

607
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:19,530
This is just a place

608
00:22:19,530 --> 00:22:20,660
to store your stuff.

609
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:21,600
Right?

610
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:23,450
That's in the future.

611
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:25,350
I'm going to be a star.

612
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:26,900
How can I let others

613
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:27,910
see my privacy?

614
00:22:28,380 --> 00:22:28,780
Right.

615
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:30,500
Privacy...

616
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:31,050
Look.

617
00:22:31,070 --> 00:22:31,680
Little Northeasterner.

618
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:32,680
We common folk...

619
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:35,340
Don't say I didn't warn you.

620
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:37,000
A bright star is

621
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,110
about to rise.

622
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:39,350
If you destroy her,

623
00:22:39,790 --> 00:22:41,110
you'll be a sinner.

624
00:22:41,350 --> 00:22:42,480
I won't forgive you.

625
00:22:43,810 --> 00:22:44,530
Well, Mr. Tao.

626
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:45,130
We are just

627
00:22:45,550 --> 00:22:46,740
discussing our business.

628
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:48,550
Let's talk later if you need something.

629
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:49,030
I know.

630
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:52,050
I'm seeing an injustice

631
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,770
and stepping in to help.

632
00:22:54,090 --> 00:22:55,220
One person in her room,

633
00:22:55,220 --> 00:22:55,960
one person in mine.

634
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:57,270
Two issues become one.

635
00:22:57,530 --> 00:22:58,630
Can you solve it?

636
00:23:01,730 --> 00:23:02,310
Girl,

637
00:23:03,110 --> 00:23:03,940
leave this matter

638
00:23:03,940 --> 00:23:04,610
to me.

639
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,460
Don't cry, don't be upset.

640
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:07,520
I'll handle it.

641
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:09,430
Just make do for 2 days, okay?

642
00:23:10,810 --> 00:23:12,610
If it weren't so close to the set,

643
00:23:13,010 --> 00:23:14,940
I wouldn't settle for a single day.

644
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:16,750
Right.

645
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,960
We won't settle for a single day.

646
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:20,730
What are you going to do?

647
00:23:20,730 --> 00:23:21,590
Give me an explanation.

648
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:22,810
Little Northeasterner,

649
00:23:22,810 --> 00:23:24,050
the new guy in our room

650
00:23:24,610 --> 00:23:26,470
really doesn't follow the rules.

651
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:27,680
That's not Room 108's rule.

652
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,680
That's the rule at Seasons Change Hotel.

653
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:30,880
Everyone is watching.

654
00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:31,220
Right?

655
00:23:31,220 --> 00:23:31,700
If a place

656
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:32,430
doesn't have rules,

657
00:23:32,430 --> 00:23:34,430
no one can live here forever, right?

658
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,440
What's wrong?

659
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:37,940
Perfect. Zongbao is back.

660
00:23:37,940 --> 00:23:38,980
-Come on.
-What’s wrong?

661
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:40,810
Give the three of us an explanation today.

662
00:23:40,810 --> 00:23:42,420
What? What explanation?

663
00:23:44,740 --> 00:23:45,570
Gentlemen.

664
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:47,320
I'll give you a suggestion.

665
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:49,010
Each of you

666
00:23:49,090 --> 00:23:50,330
pays an extra 2 yuan a day

667
00:23:50,330 --> 00:23:51,560
to book

668
00:23:51,590 --> 00:23:52,590
the remaining bed.

669
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:54,270
If I bring anyone else in,

670
00:23:54,740 --> 00:23:55,680
I'm a bastard.

671
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:56,270
Deal?

672
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:58,490
Wait. What are you doing?

673
00:23:58,610 --> 00:24:00,270
I have to pay extra?

674
00:24:00,330 --> 00:24:02,460
Wouldn't I be working for nothing all day?

675
00:24:02,460 --> 00:24:03,700
In your room,

676
00:24:04,250 --> 00:24:04,980
someone moves in,

677
00:24:04,980 --> 00:24:06,070
and you squeeze them out.

678
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:06,720
Someone moves in,

679
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:08,120
and you squeeze them out.

680
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:09,160
Am I supposed to run a business

681
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:10,050
or not?

682
00:24:10,550 --> 00:24:11,150
Everyone.

683
00:24:11,460 --> 00:24:12,720
You're all here today.

684
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,220
Let me make this clear.

685
00:24:15,110 --> 00:24:16,240
If you think

686
00:24:16,310 --> 00:24:17,810
the person living in your room

687
00:24:17,810 --> 00:24:19,640
is an eyesore and want them out,

688
00:24:20,070 --> 00:24:21,320
pay for the bed.

689
00:24:21,750 --> 00:24:23,020
I won't

690
00:24:23,460 --> 00:24:24,270
say a word.

691
00:24:53,420 --> 00:24:58,130
[East Shore Club]

692
00:25:07,570 --> 00:25:09,970
[East Shore]

693
00:25:29,010 --> 00:25:29,470
Thanks.

694
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:46,290
Buddy,

695
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:49,400
I've held my tongue for 2 days.

696
00:25:50,290 --> 00:25:51,820
We're painting an archway.

697
00:25:51,830 --> 00:25:52,560
That blue...

698
00:25:52,590 --> 00:25:53,920
we can't be this sloppy.

699
00:25:54,070 --> 00:25:55,070
For the outlines,

700
00:25:55,070 --> 00:25:56,180
you need solid color.

701
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:57,740
You have to use first-grade indigo.

702
00:25:57,740 --> 00:25:58,030
Right?

703
00:25:58,030 --> 00:25:59,070
For the center and background,

704
00:25:59,070 --> 00:26:00,180
shouldn't you use second-grade indigo?

705
00:26:00,180 --> 00:26:01,810
Then for the shading and details,

706
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:03,180
you need third-grade indigo.

707
00:26:03,180 --> 00:26:04,380
Our ancestors passed this down.

708
00:26:04,380 --> 00:26:05,720
This is how archways should be painted.

709
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:07,110
So after centuries of wind and sun,

710
00:26:07,110 --> 00:26:08,110
the base color remains.

711
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:09,850
The Forbidden City,
Summer Palace, the Imperial College...

712
00:26:09,850 --> 00:26:11,110
they're all like this.

713
00:26:11,420 --> 00:26:12,500
I'm an oil painter,

714
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:13,610
and even I know this.

715
00:26:13,610 --> 00:26:14,570
If we paint it like this...

716
00:26:14,570 --> 00:26:15,240
Man,

717
00:26:15,980 --> 00:26:17,400
we've stooped to painting this.

718
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:18,660
Why are you so serious?

719
00:26:18,850 --> 00:26:20,100
It's just a job.

720
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:22,180
I just consider myself a house painter.

721
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:23,250
Just do your own work.

722
00:26:23,250 --> 00:26:24,110
Leave me alone.

723
00:26:24,830 --> 00:26:26,430
You're not the one paying me.

724
00:26:30,210 --> 00:26:33,070
[Seasons Change Hotel]

725
00:26:43,250 --> 00:26:44,250
I'm done reading.

726
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,160
Let me make this clear first.

727
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,250
I'm an actress.

728
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,350
If I get the itch to act,

729
00:27:03,940 --> 00:27:04,790
in the middle of the night,

730
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,120
I might perform a scene.

731
00:27:06,850 --> 00:27:07,780
Act all you want.

732
00:27:10,290 --> 00:27:12,010
Let me be clearer.

733
00:27:14,110 --> 00:27:15,030
In a few days,

734
00:27:16,140 --> 00:27:18,100
I'm playing a brutal killer.

735
00:27:18,740 --> 00:27:20,270
If I get too into character,

736
00:27:20,460 --> 00:27:22,260
I might lose touch with reality.

737
00:27:22,660 --> 00:27:24,790
Then you'd better keep them separate.

738
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,220
Otherwise, the police

739
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:27,450
will have to help you.

740
00:27:27,590 --> 00:27:28,280
I still

741
00:27:28,550 --> 00:27:29,890
suggest you move out

742
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:30,960
for your own sake.

743
00:27:31,050 --> 00:27:32,180
If...

744
00:27:34,500 --> 00:27:35,720
You'll be in trouble.

745
00:27:41,090 --> 00:27:43,110
As for my books and magazines,

746
00:27:43,420 --> 00:27:44,950
you can read them whenever.

747
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:46,470
But don't get them dirty

748
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:47,920
or crease the pages.

749
00:27:53,700 --> 00:27:54,900
When I become famous,

750
00:27:55,290 --> 00:27:57,150
I'll be the star of this magazine.

751
00:27:57,330 --> 00:27:58,750
I'll give you an autograph then.

752
00:27:58,750 --> 00:28:00,550
Don't make me wait until I'm old.

753
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:10,640
What music?

754
00:28:11,220 --> 00:28:12,010
What music?

755
00:28:12,310 --> 00:28:13,370
What opportunity?

756
00:28:13,810 --> 00:28:14,870
What opportunity?

757
00:28:15,770 --> 00:28:16,790
What...

758
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:19,180
What opportunity?

759
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:29,350
Taking over the nest.

760
00:28:29,660 --> 00:28:31,460
You've only been here a few days,

761
00:28:32,030 --> 00:28:34,180
and you're already acting like the boss.

762
00:28:34,180 --> 00:28:35,770
You shouldn't be so selfish.

763
00:28:35,770 --> 00:28:37,460
You have to leave yourself a way out.

764
00:28:37,460 --> 00:28:39,010
You guys weren't here just now.

765
00:28:39,010 --> 00:28:40,610
I was afraid the oscillating fan

766
00:28:40,610 --> 00:28:41,610
was just blowing air for nothing.

767
00:28:41,610 --> 00:28:42,960
Do you believe that yourself?

768
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:43,890
A big guy like me—

769
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:45,360
didn't you see me come in?

770
00:28:45,980 --> 00:28:48,040
Didn't you see me standing by the fan?

771
00:28:48,590 --> 00:28:50,510
Then let me salute you.

772
00:28:56,530 --> 00:28:57,990
We're all a bunch of moles,

773
00:28:58,010 --> 00:28:59,060
living in a cave.

774
00:28:59,250 --> 00:29:00,180
You have to learn

775
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:01,980
to share the breeze.

776
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:03,090
Well said.

777
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,260
A bunch of moles

778
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:06,540
living in a cave...

779
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:09,830
Living just like moles.

780
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:13,190
Didn't you, the mole, say we should

781
00:29:13,350 --> 00:29:14,350
share the breeze?

782
00:29:16,420 --> 00:29:18,020
Living like moles.

783
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,220
Your share of the breeze, mole,

784
00:29:19,220 --> 00:29:20,050
you already

785
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:21,920
finished enjoying it.

786
00:29:26,090 --> 00:29:27,590
Living like moles.

787
00:29:36,420 --> 00:29:37,810
That little thing of yours

788
00:29:37,810 --> 00:29:38,670
is pretty cute,

789
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,090
but it's a lot of trouble.

790
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:42,660
If you don't keep it clean,

791
00:29:42,830 --> 00:29:44,110
it spreads germs easily.

792
00:29:44,110 --> 00:29:45,220
Don't talk nonsense.

793
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:46,280
He can understand.

794
00:29:46,460 --> 00:29:47,920
He's my son, Cao Xiaosong.

795
00:29:48,570 --> 00:29:49,570
I was just saying.

796
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,940
It's for your own good.

797
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:52,790
We're living in a place like this,

798
00:29:52,790 --> 00:29:54,050
why be so fussy?

799
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:55,440
Talking about germs.

800
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:56,100
You...

801
00:29:56,380 --> 00:29:58,030
If you're so capable,
go live in a big hotel.

802
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:58,960
Germs, my foot.

803
00:29:59,610 --> 00:30:00,310
Cao.

804
00:30:01,070 --> 00:30:01,800
You're back.

805
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:02,330
Zongbao.

806
00:30:02,330 --> 00:30:02,860
Zongbao.

807
00:30:04,140 --> 00:30:05,230
Writing a letter?

808
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:07,710
I'm revising the script.

809
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:09,740
Revising the script?

810
00:30:12,790 --> 00:30:13,500
I gotta say,

811
00:30:14,220 --> 00:30:16,480
your handwriting is really impressive.

812
00:30:19,980 --> 00:30:20,380
Bro,

813
00:30:21,380 --> 00:30:22,640
you go hustle
the film studio all the time.

814
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:24,440
Have you heard of Director Weng?

815
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,550
In our line of work,

816
00:30:25,550 --> 00:30:26,480
who doesn't know

817
00:30:26,850 --> 00:30:27,920
Director Weng?

818
00:30:31,050 --> 00:30:33,850
Are you writing a script for him?

819
00:30:37,370 --> 00:30:39,180
[To Director Weng]

820
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:43,830
So you're a professional screenwriter.

821
00:30:45,910 --> 00:30:51,670
[Jinhai Seafood Processing Plant Award]

822
00:30:49,460 --> 00:30:50,250
Semi, semi.

823
00:30:51,030 --> 00:30:52,230
Semi-professional.

824
00:30:53,260 --> 00:30:54,180
That works too.

825
00:30:54,290 --> 00:30:56,120
So half of it is professional.

826
00:30:56,770 --> 00:30:59,970
So, about your script...

827
00:31:00,460 --> 00:31:02,980
Is there a role I can play?

828
00:31:05,980 --> 00:31:07,720
The thing is, I don't know you very well.

829
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:08,330
I don't know what...

830
00:31:08,330 --> 00:31:08,850
It's okay.

831
00:31:08,850 --> 00:31:09,880
No problem.

832
00:31:10,270 --> 00:31:10,740
Come.

833
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:13,090
Sit, sit. Come.

834
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:15,770
Let's get to know each other properly.

835
00:31:16,090 --> 00:31:17,740
I'm Guo Zongbao.

836
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,840
My ancestral home is He'nan.

837
00:31:20,310 --> 00:31:22,500
My debut work...

838
00:31:22,810 --> 00:31:25,010
was the new version of

839
00:31:25,900 --> 00:31:27,480
Plain Ranger Team.

840
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:30,550
I played the captain.

841
00:31:31,330 --> 00:31:32,730
You played Li Xiangyang?

842
00:31:33,110 --> 00:31:33,350
No.

843
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:35,900
That's the guerrilla captain.

844
00:31:35,980 --> 00:31:38,310
I was the district squad captain.

845
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:41,030
Who are you kidding?

846
00:31:42,140 --> 00:31:43,340
You're just an extra.

847
00:31:43,570 --> 00:31:44,960
What extra?

848
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:46,790
A guest actor.

849
00:31:47,350 --> 00:31:48,440
I even had lines.

850
00:31:48,900 --> 00:31:50,100
I said, "Charge!"

851
00:31:50,330 --> 00:31:51,640
Those big stars

852
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:52,790
ran like rabbits.

853
00:31:52,940 --> 00:31:54,870
Whoosh, whoosh! They charged out.

854
00:31:55,220 --> 00:31:56,610
Let me show you stills.

855
00:32:04,850 --> 00:32:05,180
Here.

856
00:32:05,900 --> 00:32:06,500
That's me.

857
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:08,010
I was thin back then.

858
00:32:08,350 --> 00:32:09,670
Beijing puts meat on your bones.

859
00:32:09,030 --> 00:32:10,760
[1989 Commemoration]

860
00:32:10,420 --> 00:32:11,820
The director told me,

861
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:13,540
my performance was

862
00:32:13,570 --> 00:32:15,220
relaxed yet powerful.

863
00:32:16,210 --> 00:32:17,840
I have standards

864
00:32:18,110 --> 00:32:19,580
for my own acting.

865
00:32:20,270 --> 00:32:21,000
Bro,

866
00:32:21,350 --> 00:32:22,950
write me a role

867
00:32:22,980 --> 00:32:24,810
that lets me surpass myself.

868
00:32:25,030 --> 00:32:25,940
Yeah, right!

869
00:32:28,420 --> 00:32:28,990
Zongbao.

870
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:31,700
When Liangliang comes back and sees

871
00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:32,980
you've defected,

872
00:32:33,740 --> 00:32:34,750
he'll smack you.

873
00:32:38,250 --> 00:32:39,330
Besides, can't you see

874
00:32:39,330 --> 00:32:40,350
he's not interested in you?

875
00:32:40,350 --> 00:32:40,960
You're kissing

876
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,490
-up to him...
-Don’t worry.

877
00:32:43,220 --> 00:32:44,980
I've noted your request.

878
00:32:45,310 --> 00:32:46,440
I'll keep it in mind.

879
00:32:46,590 --> 00:32:47,570
Thanks.

880
00:32:48,090 --> 00:32:50,000
Take it to heart.

881
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:50,970
Don't worry.

882
00:32:51,140 --> 00:32:52,030
Alright then.

883
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:52,940
Well,

884
00:32:53,180 --> 00:32:54,330
keep revising.

885
00:32:54,530 --> 00:32:56,390
I've been around the film studio.

886
00:32:56,490 --> 00:32:57,180
I know.

887
00:32:57,380 --> 00:32:58,660
Screenwriting

888
00:32:58,830 --> 00:32:59,640
isn't easy.

889
00:33:00,330 --> 00:33:01,480
Writing one

890
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:03,540
takes 2 or 3 years.

891
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:06,640
If things go wrong, 3 to 5 years.

892
00:33:07,380 --> 00:33:10,050
Worst case, 10 years.

893
00:33:11,050 --> 00:33:12,250
No matter what you do,

894
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:13,460
life is tough,

895
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:15,320
and money is hard to earn.

896
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:18,210
Some even take 10 years?

897
00:33:23,250 --> 00:33:24,110
Let me tell you,

898
00:33:24,110 --> 00:33:24,970
you must hold in

899
00:33:24,980 --> 00:33:25,850
that dialect of yours.

900
00:33:25,850 --> 00:33:27,090
Don't let it slip out. Do you hear me?

901
00:33:27,090 --> 00:33:28,220
Okay, Director Cui.

902
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:28,960
And,

903
00:33:29,420 --> 00:33:30,290
you must relax.

904
00:33:30,610 --> 00:33:31,610
Don't be nervous.

905
00:33:32,330 --> 00:33:33,090
Clear your mind.

906
00:33:33,090 --> 00:33:33,880
And immerse yourself

907
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:34,590
in the role.

908
00:33:35,030 --> 00:33:36,230
Don't worry, Mr. Cui.

909
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:37,400
I'm a professional.

910
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,260
Good. Confidence is a good thing.

911
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:41,110
The assistant casting director here

912
00:33:41,110 --> 00:33:42,010
is a buddy of mine.

913
00:33:42,010 --> 00:33:43,050
I've put in a good word.

914
00:33:43,050 --> 00:33:44,510
Just focus on your acting.

915
00:33:44,700 --> 00:33:45,740
Thank you, Mr. Cui.

916
00:33:45,740 --> 00:33:46,740
Don't mention it.

917
00:33:47,110 --> 00:33:48,590
Your teacher is my buddy too.

918
00:33:48,590 --> 00:33:48,960
Go on.

919
00:33:51,940 --> 00:33:55,160
[Love Debt Filming Team]

920
00:33:53,920 --> 00:33:54,660
Come in.

921
00:33:59,660 --> 00:34:00,750
A girl from Huzhou.

922
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:02,210
Hello, Director.

923
00:34:01,590 --> 00:34:08,090
[Character settings]

924
00:34:02,500 --> 00:34:03,140
Hello.

925
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:04,440
I... I am Shen Ranran.

926
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,070
Shen Ranran.

927
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,360
Huzhou, Zhejiang.

928
00:34:11,880 --> 00:34:13,760
You were in 2 movies.

929
00:34:15,670 --> 00:34:17,199
When will they be released?

930
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,050
I don't know yet.

931
00:34:21,500 --> 00:34:23,230
No wonder I haven't seen them.

932
00:34:24,110 --> 00:34:25,760
I heard she's good.

933
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:28,610
You heard?

934
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:30,780
Yes.

935
00:34:32,380 --> 00:34:32,780
Okay.

936
00:34:34,710 --> 00:34:35,530
Do you know each other?

937
00:34:35,530 --> 00:34:36,730
Or have you worked together?

938
00:34:36,730 --> 00:34:37,150
No.

939
00:34:37,570 --> 00:34:39,630
Assistant Director Cui introduced her.

940
00:34:39,630 --> 00:34:40,159
Alright.

941
00:34:40,610 --> 00:34:41,360
Pick a scene.

942
00:34:42,730 --> 00:34:43,610
Let's see what you've got.

943
00:34:43,590 --> 00:34:50,650
[Character settings]

944
00:34:44,510 --> 00:34:44,940
Okay.

945
00:34:47,880 --> 00:34:48,810
Come on, Ranran.

946
00:34:49,500 --> 00:34:50,710
I've marked it for you.

947
00:34:50,710 --> 00:34:52,940
You all think you're such big shots, huh?

948
00:34:52,940 --> 00:34:54,440
You're being so picky.

949
00:34:55,130 --> 00:34:55,980
Let me tell you,

950
00:34:55,980 --> 00:34:57,860
you're just fillers. Understand?

951
00:34:57,860 --> 00:34:59,170
But not for free.

952
00:34:59,340 --> 00:35:00,270
You'll get paid.

953
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:02,030
Those I picked, follow me.

954
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,510
Me! Me! Me!

955
00:35:03,510 --> 00:35:04,340
You, you.

956
00:35:04,780 --> 00:35:05,460
You, you.

957
00:35:05,630 --> 00:35:06,230
That girl.

958
00:35:06,650 --> 00:35:07,450
Get on the bus.

959
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:09,960
We only need this many people today.

960
00:35:10,010 --> 00:35:11,400
Go find work elsewhere.

961
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:12,400
Clear out.

962
00:35:13,070 --> 00:35:13,730
Move along.

963
00:35:15,610 --> 00:35:16,340
I'm leaving.

964
00:35:16,650 --> 00:35:17,650
See you tomorrow.

965
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:18,340
Take care.

966
00:35:18,340 --> 00:35:18,780
Okay.

967
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:21,640
Director Wei.

968
00:35:23,590 --> 00:35:25,050
You've been working hard.

969
00:35:25,610 --> 00:35:27,210
Look at all this sweat. Here.

970
00:35:27,210 --> 00:35:28,150
Here, sit, sit.

971
00:35:28,210 --> 00:35:29,410
Sit for a while. Here.

972
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:30,210
Let me cover it.

973
00:35:30,210 --> 00:35:31,170
It's dirty.

974
00:35:31,550 --> 00:35:32,410
Here, sit down.

975
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:33,250
Please sit.

976
00:35:33,510 --> 00:35:34,510
Go away.

977
00:35:35,110 --> 00:35:35,780
I... I...

978
00:35:36,010 --> 00:35:38,630
I brought you breakfast.

979
00:35:38,900 --> 00:35:39,700
This pancake.

980
00:35:40,550 --> 00:35:41,590
-Stop.
-It’s still hot.

981
00:35:41,590 --> 00:35:42,650
I don't need your pancake.

982
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:43,930
I don't need it.

983
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,110
I've been working all morning.

984
00:35:45,110 --> 00:35:46,050
I'm already fired up enough.

985
00:35:46,050 --> 00:35:46,910
Don't choke me.

986
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:47,600
It's okay.

987
00:35:48,030 --> 00:35:49,890
I have something to cool you down.

988
00:35:50,150 --> 00:35:51,010
Mung bean soup.

989
00:35:51,230 --> 00:35:51,570
Here.

990
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:54,250
I made it myself.

991
00:35:55,300 --> 00:35:56,630
It's chilled. Drink up.

992
00:36:01,590 --> 00:36:03,000
There aren't many roles with lines.

993
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:03,590
Really?

994
00:36:04,510 --> 00:36:05,800
Watch repair shop.

995
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:09,350
Grain store counter.

996
00:36:10,260 --> 00:36:12,450
[The Last Palace Romance]

997
00:36:11,230 --> 00:36:12,360
The Last...

998
00:36:12,940 --> 00:36:13,280
This one.

999
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:13,940
The Last...

1000
00:36:15,650 --> 00:36:16,850
You're the right age.

1001
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:18,010
Really?

1002
00:36:22,780 --> 00:36:23,760
The Emperor?

1003
00:36:24,010 --> 00:36:25,920
What are you thinking? Emperor?

1004
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:27,170
Eu...

1005
00:36:27,780 --> 00:36:28,300
Eunuch.

1006
00:36:30,110 --> 00:36:31,070
The Head Eunuch.

1007
00:36:31,650 --> 00:36:33,650
Hanging around the Emperor all day.

1008
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:34,650
The camera will catch your ear,

1009
00:36:34,650 --> 00:36:35,650
or half your face.

1010
00:36:35,710 --> 00:36:37,040
Isn't that good enough?

1011
00:36:38,150 --> 00:36:38,480
Okay.

1012
00:36:39,460 --> 00:36:40,320
That works too.

1013
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:41,420
You're right.

1014
00:36:42,260 --> 00:36:44,120
If I can become

1015
00:36:44,210 --> 00:36:45,870
an expert at playing eunuchs,

1016
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:47,320
then my big break

1017
00:36:47,530 --> 00:36:48,440
won't be far off.

1018
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:49,800
5:30 tomorrow morning.

1019
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:50,540
Right here.

1020
00:36:51,260 --> 00:36:51,790
Yes, sir.

1021
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:58,210
Mom told me when I was little,

1022
00:36:57,440 --> 00:37:00,720
[All for the children]

1023
00:36:58,400 --> 00:37:03,260
the sea is my hometown.

1024
00:37:03,550 --> 00:37:08,010
Born by the sea.

1025
00:37:08,190 --> 00:37:12,230
Grew up in the sea.

1026
00:37:12,340 --> 00:37:13,590
Okay, that's enough.

1027
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,960
Your singing is quite good.

1028
00:37:16,230 --> 00:37:18,490
But do you have any teaching experience?

1029
00:37:18,550 --> 00:37:19,710
I went to a teachers' college.

1030
00:37:19,710 --> 00:37:21,360
I taught children back in my hometown.

1031
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:23,220
You know music theory too, right?

1032
00:37:23,340 --> 00:37:25,320
Let's try a class first.

1033
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:26,920
Great. Thank you.

1034
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:28,690
May I ask

1035
00:37:28,690 --> 00:37:30,220
what the monthly salary is?

1036
00:37:33,380 --> 00:37:35,380
Isn't it a bit early to ask that?

1037
00:37:37,050 --> 00:37:37,760
Excuse me.

1038
00:37:47,250 --> 00:37:48,580
There's another piece.

1039
00:37:50,980 --> 00:37:52,430
Wang, you've got a job?

1040
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:55,350
[Bicycle Repair]

1041
00:37:53,090 --> 00:37:55,070
There's plenty of work.
People are lining up.

1042
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:56,670
Lining up. Business is good.

1043
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:58,630
I picked up 2 pieces of wire.

1044
00:37:59,550 --> 00:38:00,900
I'll go get my tools.

1045
00:38:01,900 --> 00:38:03,360
You're just fixing range hoods.

1046
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:05,220
Why are you acting all secretive?

1047
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:08,540
There is no shame in working for a living.

1048
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:10,280
My roommates

1049
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:12,330
only know I'm an actor.

1050
00:38:12,610 --> 00:38:14,540
So what role did you play recently?

1051
00:38:14,590 --> 00:38:16,520
I played a high-ranking official.

1052
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,010
A high-ranking official?

1053
00:38:19,010 --> 00:38:20,820
A really high-ranking official.

1054
00:38:20,820 --> 00:38:21,780
That's great.

1055
00:38:22,610 --> 00:38:23,710
Great.

1056
00:38:28,460 --> 00:38:32,200
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

1057
00:38:29,230 --> 00:38:30,030
Wait a minute.

1058
00:38:30,110 --> 00:38:30,460
What?

1059
00:38:30,730 --> 00:38:31,880
That...

1060
00:38:31,980 --> 00:38:33,780
really high-ranking official.

1061
00:38:34,010 --> 00:38:35,610
What kind of official was it?

1062
00:38:38,260 --> 00:38:39,160
A eunuch.

1063
00:38:40,590 --> 00:38:43,400
Well, a eunuch counts as an official?

1064
00:38:44,690 --> 00:38:45,760
A eunuch is an official?

1065
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:49,150
Repairing range hoods!

1066
00:38:49,860 --> 00:38:52,710
Unclogging drains!

1067
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:58,950
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

1068
00:38:56,130 --> 00:38:58,170
Be careful. Slow down.

1069
00:38:58,340 --> 00:39:01,200
Repairing range hoods!

1070
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:03,460
Unclogging drains!

1071
00:39:03,520 --> 00:39:05,710
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

1072
00:39:04,630 --> 00:39:05,920
Excuse me.

1073
00:39:06,230 --> 00:39:06,760
Thanks.

1074
00:39:07,210 --> 00:39:11,690
Ah, ah, ah...

1075
00:39:12,980 --> 00:39:17,150
Ribbit, ribbit, ribbit...

1076
00:39:17,300 --> 00:39:18,420
Is that your child?

1077
00:39:18,650 --> 00:39:20,550
My youngest son has always been naughty.

1078
00:39:20,550 --> 00:39:21,860
He looks well-behaved.

1079
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:22,380
Not at all.

1080
00:39:22,380 --> 00:39:23,170
Be serious.

1081
00:39:23,170 --> 00:39:23,940
He's a handful.

1082
00:39:23,940 --> 00:39:25,200
Kids are all like that.

1083
00:39:25,730 --> 00:39:27,330
He makes friends instantly.

1084
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:28,420
Come on.

1085
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:29,920
Come here.

1086
00:39:31,070 --> 00:39:32,100
What's your name?

1087
00:39:32,130 --> 00:39:34,050
My name is Frog. Ribbit, ribbit.

1088
00:39:35,570 --> 00:39:36,960
You mean the water kid
from Calabash Brothers

1089
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:38,240
—the fifth one?

1090
00:39:38,460 --> 00:39:38,900
Yes.

1091
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:40,560
Then you're amazing.

1092
00:39:40,610 --> 00:39:42,610
You can suck in water and spit it out.

1093
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:44,730
When the water kid sucks in water,

1094
00:39:44,730 --> 00:39:46,330
where does it go? Do you know?

1095
00:39:46,460 --> 00:39:47,040
Here.

1096
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:48,950
Let me see.

1097
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:50,420
Show me how you suck it in.

1098
00:39:50,420 --> 00:39:51,000
Okay?

1099
00:39:51,130 --> 00:39:51,460
Okay.

1100
00:39:51,460 --> 00:39:53,800
Come on. 1, 2, 3. Suck.

1101
00:39:55,590 --> 00:39:59,380
Ah, ah, ah...

1102
00:39:59,380 --> 00:40:01,390
Awesome. Well done.

1103
00:40:02,010 --> 00:40:03,810
Show them how it's done. Come on.

1104
00:40:05,340 --> 00:40:06,940
This teacher is pretty good.

1105
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:08,070
We just hired her.

1106
00:40:08,070 --> 00:40:08,670
She's new?

1107
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:09,940
Did he do a good job? Right.

1108
00:40:09,940 --> 00:40:10,510
Good.

1109
00:40:10,510 --> 00:40:11,910
Let's give him a big hand.

1110
00:40:12,110 --> 00:40:12,690
Awesome.

1111
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:13,730
Come on, go back to your seat.

1112
00:40:13,730 --> 00:40:15,460
Let's do it all together, okay?

1113
00:40:15,780 --> 00:40:16,730
Okay.

1114
00:40:16,820 --> 00:40:17,710
She's a really good teacher.

1115
00:40:17,710 --> 00:40:18,440
Pretty good.

1116
00:40:18,980 --> 00:40:19,530
Come on.

1117
00:40:21,630 --> 00:40:26,550
Ah, ah, ah...

1118
00:40:28,500 --> 00:40:30,210
The waves surge,

1119
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:33,610
drifting with me everywhere.

1120
00:40:35,570 --> 00:40:36,800
You got good news?

1121
00:40:36,960 --> 00:40:37,840
So childish.

1122
00:40:39,070 --> 00:40:40,270
You're even singing.

1123
00:40:41,070 --> 00:40:43,500
I finally found a job today.

1124
00:40:45,190 --> 00:40:46,860
But I won't get paid
until the end of the month.

1125
00:40:46,860 --> 00:40:48,480
I'll pay you back right away then.

1126
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:49,280
I told you,

1127
00:40:49,340 --> 00:40:50,940
no need to rush to pay me back.

1128
00:40:51,050 --> 00:40:52,510
I'm not that short on cash.

1129
00:40:53,010 --> 00:40:54,810
But finding a job is a good thing.

1130
00:40:55,190 --> 00:40:57,890
It's the first step
to finding your footing.

1131
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,220
I'm nowhere near that yet.

1132
00:41:01,730 --> 00:41:03,380
At best,

1133
00:41:06,820 --> 00:41:08,080
I'm just on my tiptoes.

1134
00:41:09,030 --> 00:41:09,830
Here, douzhi.

1135
00:41:11,070 --> 00:41:13,150
So this is Beijing douzhi.

1136
00:41:13,170 --> 00:41:14,570
Wait. You smell it first.

1137
00:41:23,500 --> 00:41:24,500
Like stinky tofu.

1138
00:41:24,500 --> 00:41:26,090
Smells stinky, tastes good.

1139
00:41:26,090 --> 00:41:26,550
Really?

1140
00:41:40,460 --> 00:41:41,360
A real hero takes 3 sips.

1141
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:42,360
I'll drink first.

1142
00:41:49,210 --> 00:41:50,460
No, no, no. Yours...

1143
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:51,620
Let me smell it.

1144
00:42:07,430 --> 00:42:07,960
How is it?

1145
00:42:12,820 --> 00:42:14,220
Can you singing students

1146
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:16,050
turn off your sense of taste?

1147
00:42:16,050 --> 00:42:17,510
Can't you taste anything?

1148
00:42:18,570 --> 00:42:19,230
Keep going.

1149
00:42:33,500 --> 00:42:35,630
Are you spitting it out or drinking it?

1150
00:42:37,690 --> 00:42:38,290
It's good.

1151
00:42:39,500 --> 00:42:40,100
It's good?

1152
00:42:40,190 --> 00:42:40,690
It's good.

1153
00:42:40,690 --> 00:42:41,440
Have another bowl.

1154
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:41,760
No.

1155
00:42:42,170 --> 00:42:42,780
I'll get you another bowl.

1156
00:42:42,780 --> 00:42:44,130
No, don't.

1157
00:42:44,230 --> 00:42:45,050
I'm full.

1158
00:42:48,090 --> 00:42:49,070
Didn't you say it was good?
